reviews.text:
This is a small establishment on the second level of  Causeway Bay Plaza. They offer a nicely prized set lunch. Coffee is good. 

Service here is quick and efficient. As everywhere in Hong Kong, a bit of patience goes a very long way.

Update: returned for a late night dessert. It was a disappointing to be served crepes that were cold. Presentation was good but not as expected. Coffee was not spectacular either. Although, staff were accommodating.

Great place for gathering and tasting drinks and foods!
Bright and comfortable environment with large sofa with cute cushion. Good service with young staff.
We chose 2 dinner sets: Fettuccine with Diced beef fillets and green pepper sauce (so delicious with soft texture beef, perfect chewing texture with yummy green pepper sauce) and grilled chicken risotto with black truffle （soft and healthy grilled chicken with an egg yolk; risotto was good taste with full of black truffle and different types of mushroom)
For adding $30, a lovely mushroom soup is so creamy and small minced mushroom with 2 pieces of crispy toasts.
For dessert, we ordered chocolates and chestnut pancake with banana pieces, almond ice cream and nuts! Really beautiful display and yummy taste. Not so sweet and make perfectly!
I've ordered black squid ink pasta with spicy sausage, beef avocado hamburger and small hushed potato with cheese dip. All were excellent, especially the hamburger.
Food not too bad, but they really need to improve their service, they seem aggressive to every customer even its not that busy at tea time..
Orders all day breakfast.  It's filling and yummy.  Portion is just right.  Good place for chatting with friends.

reviews.text: Truly a shopping district. A tourist shopping heaven. A word of caution.... It's a very, very crowded district and is an experience walking around the streets there.
Good shopping zone.
HONGKONG FLOWERS SHOW happened every year in a month of March...different part of Asia will showcase there own creativity and designs of flowers in a large crowd at Victoria Park in Causeway Bay

Causeway Place in Causeway Bay Hong Kong is located between Sogo and Times Square.  Thus, making it 1 of the busiest area in all of Hong Kong to walk and whatnot, but it is very very appeasing to the eyes.

Reason for Causeway Place's appeal is that any and all the world's famous designers have a store front here.  From Victoria Secret to Apple is here.  

For those folks who do not like crowds or crowded places, please do not go here unless you venture out very very early in the day.  

Transportation is vast and plentiful to Causeway Place. All buses from Hong Kong do make stops in Causeway Bay.  The Hong Kong MTR station for Causeway Place is the Causeway Bay station.
A popular shopping mall located in a touristy area consisting of fashion stores and restaurants.
